[{"type":"{{","value":[["pagebanner"],["Pagebanner default.jpg"]]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["File:Bistrita.jpg"],["thumb"],["300px"],["right"],["Overview of Bistriţa"]]},"\n",{"type":"'''","value":["Bistrița"]}," is the capital of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Bistrița-Năsăud County"]]}," in northern ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Transylvania"]]},", Romania.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Understand"]},"\nBistriţa was founded in the early 13th century by German settlers and (due to its location on the main trading route with ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Moldavia"]]},") became one of Transylvania's major Medieval cities. Several interesting sites from that time survive in the city's old quarter. Some tourists are also attracted by the fact that the town was mentioned in Bram Stoker's novel ",{"type":"''","value":["Dracula"]},".\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get in"]},"\n",{"type":"===","value":["By train"]},"\nBistriţa is on a secondary railway and gets limited service: a few local trains, three commuter trains from ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Cluj"]]}," (a three hours trip) and a night train from ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Bucharest"]]}," (nine hours) via ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Brasov"]]}," . Timetables can be found on the website of the railway operator CFR  ",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.cfr.ro\/calatori\/"]},"\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By car"]},"\nBistriţa is located on the DN17 road linking ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Transylvania"]]}," with ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Southern Bukovina"],["Southern Bucovina"]]},".\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By bus"]},"\nThere are frequent buses from  Cluj (two hours travel time), three-four buses from ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Suceava"]]}," (four hours and half), ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Târgu Mureş"]]}," (three hours) and one bus from ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Iaşi"]]}," (seven hours). Some of their schedules are available on autogari.ro ",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.autogari.ro\/?&lang=UK"]},".\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get around"]},"\nThe relatively compact old quarter can be visited on foot. The rest of the city is covered by several minibus lines operated by ",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.transmixtbn.ro\/harta_retelei Transmixt"]}]},".\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["See"]},"\n",{"type":"===","value":["Landmarks"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Turnul Dogarilor"],["alt=Cooper's tower"],["url="],["email="],["address=strada Dogarilor nr. 18"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=One of the few remaining parts of Bistriţa's medieval fortifications, it now houses a dolls and masks museum"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Sugălete"],["alt=Sugălete row"],["url="],["email="],["address=Piaţa Centrală"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=A group of thirteen connected homes built in the 14th-16th centuries"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Casa Ion Zidaru"],["url="],["email="],["address=Piaţa Centrală nr. 30"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=One of the best examples of late Gothic architecture in Transylvania"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Casa Argintarului"],["alt=Silversmith's house"],["url="],["email="],["address=strada Dornei nr. 5"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=A beautiful 16th century Renaissance house"]]}]},{"type":"===","value":["Religious sites"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Biserica Evanghelică"],["alt=Evangelical church"],["url="],["email="],["address=Piaţa Centrală"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=First built in the second half of the 14th